Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek grey ware large pottery vessel, probably a krater or dinos; dark grey fabric with numerous mica inclusions; dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Sherd joins British Museum 1965,0930.407; probably belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1965,0930.408; 1965,0930.409; 1965,0930.410.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.013)
